    {
      "id": 17,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [40, 520],
      "size": [780, 560],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 0,
      "mode": 0,
      "properties": {"text": ""},
      "widgets_values": [
        "DEPTH BACKEND COMPARISON — Depth Anything V2 vs Depth Anything 3, ONE solve\n\nOne AtlasLearnedSolveFromImage provides the camera for BOTH branches, so the\nonly variable in this graph is the depth model: the two AtlasDepthMap nodes\n(V2 Outdoor on top, DA3METRIC-LARGE below) are literally the only difference.\nEverything downstream is duplicated with identical settings.\n\nWhat to compare after one Queue:\n\n1. DEPTH PREVIEWS (left column) — structure/noise on flat surfaces, thin\n   details, sky. Both are min-max normalized per image for viewing: compare\n   STRUCTURE, not absolute brightness.\n\n2. HOLE MASKS (middle) — the mesh's own gap data: white pixels are exactly\n   where 📽 Project will show black (silhouette tears + sky + invalid depth).\n   Less spurious white INSIDE continuous surfaces = better local depth.\n   First A/B on the 4K test images: DA3 cut torn_fraction ~3x on 2 of 4\n   images and kept a mesh (4240 faces) where V2 shattered to 0 faces on a\n   steep-pitch shot; parity on a very long lens. See\n   docs/dev/da3_backend_test_plan.md for the full protocol + results log.\n\n3. VIEWPORTS (right) — 📽 Project is on by default; orbit BOTH viewports off\n   the recovered view and compare where the projection breaks into holes.\n   Same relief_grid 128 / depth_edge_rel 0.5 on both meshes.\n\nNotes:\n- DA3 models need the [neural-da3] extra. Into a ComfyUI venv install with\n  --no-deps (DA3's own deps pin numpy<2 and would downgrade ComfyUI's numpy)\n  — see INSTALL.md 'Optional Depth Anything 3 Backend'.\n- The solve is wired into every depth node's optional 'solve' input, so\n  DA3METRIC converts canonical depth to metres with the SOLVED focal\n  (focal_source='solve'). That focal comes from GeoCalib — independent of\n  whichever depth model the solve node used — so it is valid for both\n  branches; V2 ignores it entirely. Unwired, DA3METRIC falls back to an\n  assumed normal-lens focal (focal_source='assumed' — it is a depth-only\n  head and predicts no camera); the relief meshes re-pin metric scale to\n  the solve's ground either way (estimate_ground_scale). Solve-bearing nodes\n  (AtlasDeriveProjectionGeometry, AtlasExportReliefMesh, the patch/occlusion\n  nodes and the learned solve's own height measurement) pass the SOLVED\n  focal instead (focal_source='solve').\n- The solve node's own depth_model is left at V2 deliberately: its tier-2\n  camera-height measurement then uses the same model for any run of this\n  graph, keeping the shared camera identical while you switch either\n  branch's model. To test DA3's height measurement itself, change the SOLVE\n  node's depth_model too (it accepts the same DA3 ids).\n- DA3NESTED-GIANT-LARGE-1.1 also appears in the combos but is CC BY-NC 4.0\n  (non-commercial) and 1.4B params; DA3MONO-LARGE is relative-only."
      ]
    }
